        <h3>Topography</h3>
        The Amhara area is situated in the northwest of Ethiopia around 9°–14° N and 36°–40° E. Three main agricultural climatic zones make up the region: lowland (below 1,500 metres above sea level), semi-highland (1,500 to 2,300 metres above sea level), highland (above 2,300 metres above sea level), which account for 20%, 44%, and 28% of the total. Diversified agriculture thrives in this diverse ecosystem. The terrain of the area is made up of plains, gorges, plateaus and hills. The highest point in the area is 4,620 metres, which is located at the summit of Ras Dashen. The lowest point is 500 metres. Africa's fourth-highest peak, Ras Dashen peak, is located in the North Gondar administrative zone. 

      </p>
